  <titles>
    <title as="introduced" type="short">Prescription Coverage Now Act of 2006</title>
    <title as="introduced" type="official">To amend part D of title XVIII of the Social Security Act to assist low-income individuals in obtaining subsidized prescription drug coverage under the Medicare prescription drug program by expediting the application and qualification process, by increasing the maximum permissible resource level for eligibility for such subsidies, and by waiving any late enrollment penalty for the first 24 uncovered months.</title>
